## 1. Introduction

### 1.1 Scope

This change request addresses a critical bug in the kiro-ts Anthropic converter module where tool\_use\_id values become mismatched between the streaming response sent to the VS Code extension client and the conversation history stored internally by kiro-ts. This mismatch causes all ReAct tool continuation requests to fail with HTTP 400 Bad Request errors, effectively breaking the entire Chat Panel tool-calling loop for the Kiro provider.

The scope includes: - Identifying the root cause of tool\_use\_id mismatch in the Anthropic format converter - Ensuring consistent tool\_use\_id values between streaming responses and internal history - Restoring full ReAct tool loop functionality for the Chat Panel

### 1.2 Out of Scope

* Changes to the VS Code extension tool execution logic
* Changes to the Kiro Q API backend
* Other streaming formats (non-Anthropic)
* Tool discovery/registration mechanisms
* Non-tool-calling chat interactions (plain text streaming works correctly)

### 1.3 Preliminary Requirement

* Access to kiro-ts source code (src/anthropic/converter.ts or handlers.ts)
* Understanding of the Kiro Q API response format and Anthropic message format differences
* Test environment capable of triggering multi-turn tool-calling conversations

## 2. Business Requirements

### 2.1 High Level Process Map

The ReAct tool loop involves multiple components working in sequence. When a user sends a chat message that triggers tool usage, the system must maintain consistent identifiers throughout the entire request-response-continuation cycle.

Use Case Diagram [*Edit in draw.io*](diagrams/use-case.drawio)

Business Flow [*Edit in draw.io*](diagrams/business-flow.drawio)

**Current (Broken) Flow:**

1. User sends chatWithTools request via extension
2. kiro-ts forwards request to Kiro Q API
3. Kiro Q API returns tool\_use response with id=tooluse\_490C (example)
4. kiro-ts converter transforms response to streaming format — assigns DIFFERENT id (e.g., tooluse\_DWlP) in the stream sent to extension
5. kiro-ts stores tooluse\_490C in internal conversation history
6. Extension executes tool, sends continuation with toolResult.toolUseId = tooluse\_DWlP (from streaming response)
7. kiro-ts receives continuation — looks for tooluse\_DWlP in history — NOT FOUND
8. kiro-ts skips orphan tool\_result → sends malformed request to Kiro Q API → **400 Bad Request**

**Expected (Fixed) Flow:**

1. User sends chatWithTools request via extension
2. kiro-ts forwards request to Kiro Q API
3. Kiro Q API returns tool\_use response with id=tooluse\_XYZ
4. kiro-ts converter uses THE SAME tooluse\_XYZ in both streaming response AND internal history
5. Extension executes tool, sends continuation with toolResult.toolUseId = tooluse\_XYZ
6. kiro-ts matches tool\_result to history entry — SUCCESS
7. kiro-ts constructs valid continuation request → Kiro Q API returns next response

### 2.2 List of User Stories / Use Cases

| # | Story / Use Case / Epic | Priority | Source Ticket |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| 1 | As a developer using Kiro Chat Panel, I want tool-calling (ReAct loop) to work correctly so that the AI can use tools to assist me | MUST HAVE | KSA-236 |
| 2 | As a developer, I want consistent tool\_use\_id values between the streaming response and internal history so that continuation requests succeed | MUST HAVE | KSA-236 |
| 3 | As a developer, I want clear error diagnostics when tool continuation fails so that I can identify the root cause | SHOULD HAVE | KSA-236 |

### 2.3 Details of User Stories

#### Business Flow

**Step 1:** Developer opens Kiro Chat Panel and sends a message that requires tool usage (e.g., “read file X and analyze it”)

**Step 2:** Extension packages the message as a chatWithTools request and sends to kiro-ts

**Step 3:** kiro-ts converts the request from extension format to Kiro Q API format and forwards it

**Step 4:** Kiro Q API processes the request and returns a tool\_use content block with a unique tool\_use\_id

**Step 5:** kiro-ts converter transforms the Kiro Q response back to extension streaming format, preserving the SAME tool\_use\_id

**Step 6:** kiro-ts stores the assistant message (including tool\_use\_id) in conversation history

**Step 7:** Extension receives the streaming response, identifies the tool call, executes the tool locally

**Step 8:** Extension sends a continuation request with toolResult containing the matching tool\_use\_id

**Step 9:** kiro-ts receives the continuation, matches the tool\_use\_id against history, constructs the next API request

**Step 10:** Cycle repeats until the model produces a final text response (no more tool calls)

**Note:** The critical invariant is that tool\_use\_id MUST be identical in: (a) streaming response to client, (b) conversation history stored in kiro-ts, and (c) continuation request from client.

#### STORY 1: Fix tool\_use\_id Consistency in ReAct Loop

As a developer using Kiro Chat Panel, I want tool-calling (ReAct loop) to work correctly so that the AI can use tools to assist me.

**Requirement Details:**

1. The kiro-ts Anthropic converter MUST use the same tool\_use\_id value when converting between Kiro Q API format and the streaming response format sent to the extension
2. The tool\_use\_id stored in kiro-ts internal conversation history MUST match the tool\_use\_id sent in the streaming response to the client
3. When the extension sends a continuation request with a toolResult.toolUseId, kiro-ts MUST successfully match it against the stored history
4. The fix must handle all tool\_use responses, regardless of how many tools are called in a single response

**Data Fields (if applicable):**

| Field | Type | Required | Description | Example |
| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |
| tool\_use\_id | String | Yes | Unique identifier for a tool invocation, generated by Kiro Q API | tooluse\_490C... |
| tool\_name | String | Yes | Name of the tool being invoked | readFile |
| tool\_input | JSON Object | Yes | Parameters passed to the tool | {"path": "/src/main.rs"} |
| toolResult.toolUseId | String | Yes | ID sent back by extension in continuation, must match tool\_use\_id | tooluse\_490C... |
| toolResult.content | String/JSON | Yes | Result of tool execution | "file contents..." |

**Acceptance Criteria:**

1. GIVEN a chatWithTools request that triggers a tool\_use response, WHEN kiro-ts streams the response to the extension, THEN the tool\_use\_id in the streaming response MUST equal the tool\_use\_id from the Kiro Q API response
2. GIVEN kiro-ts stores the assistant message in history, WHEN comparing the stored tool\_use\_id with the one sent to the client, THEN they MUST be identical
3. GIVEN the extension sends a continuation with toolResult.toolUseId, WHEN kiro-ts processes it, THEN it MUST find a matching entry in history and construct a valid API request
4. GIVEN a multi-tool response (multiple tool\_use blocks), WHEN processing each block, THEN each tool\_use\_id MUST be consistent across all three locations (stream, history, continuation)
5. GIVEN the fix is applied, WHEN running a full ReAct tool loop (chat → tool\_use → tool\_result → continuation), THEN the loop MUST complete without 400 errors

**Validation Rules (if applicable):**

* tool\_use\_id must be a non-empty string
* tool\_use\_id must follow the pattern tooluse\_[A-Za-z0-9]+
* The same tool\_use\_id must never be reused across different tool invocations within a conversation

**Error Handling (if applicable):**

* If a toolResult.toolUseId does not match any entry in conversation history: log a WARNING with both the received ID and available IDs in history, return a descriptive error to the extension (not just raw 400)
* If the Kiro Q API response contains a tool\_use block without an id field: reject and log error, do not proceed with broken state

#### STORY 2: Ensure ID Passthrough in Converter

As a developer, I want consistent tool\_use\_id values between the streaming response and internal history so that continuation requests succeed.

**Requirement Details:**

1. The converter module (converter.ts) must NOT generate new/different IDs when transforming between formats
2. If the Kiro Q format uses a different field name or structure for the tool ID, the converter must correctly map it to the Anthropic tool\_use id field without creating a new value
3. The ID must be passed through as-is — no transformation, no re-encoding, no regeneration

**Acceptance Criteria:**

1. GIVEN the Kiro Q API returns tool\_use\_id = "tooluse\_ABC123", WHEN the converter processes this response, THEN both the streaming output AND history storage use exactly "tooluse\_ABC123"
2. GIVEN the converter handles format differences between Kiro Q and Anthropic formats, WHEN an ID field is mapped, THEN the VALUE must remain unchanged even if the field NAME changes
3. GIVEN a unit test with known tool\_use\_id values, WHEN running the converter, THEN input ID equals output ID in all output locations

#### STORY 3: Improve Error Diagnostics for Tool Continuation Failures

As a developer, I want clear error diagnostics when tool continuation fails so that I can identify the root cause.

**Requirement Details:**

1. When a tool\_result cannot be matched to history, the error log should include: the received toolUseId, all tool\_use\_id values currently in history, and the conversation turn number
2. The error response to the extension should indicate “tool\_use\_id mismatch” rather than a generic 400

**Acceptance Criteria:**

1. GIVEN a mismatched toolResult.toolUseId is received, WHEN kiro-ts logs the error, THEN the log entry includes the mismatched ID and available IDs for debugging
2. GIVEN a mismatch error occurs, WHEN the error is returned to the extension, THEN the error message clearly states “tool\_use\_id not found in conversation history” rather than a generic error

